      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is primarily supported by the belief that the Constitution should be interpreted according to the meaning it held at the time it was ratified. Proponents argue that the Founders intended a specific understanding of the text, and judicial interpretation should strive to capture that original public meaning. This approach aims to maintain democratic legitimacy by constraining judges from imposing their personal political views onto the law. Essentially, it roots constitutional meaning in historical texts rather than evolving societal values.",
