    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so it's kind of a gray area then. but if you look at how it's actually applied in court cases today, it seems like originalism is mostly used to roll back rights that people take for granted. like, is it even a legitimate way to interpret the law if it just ends up serving a specific partisan outcome every time?",
